<paragraph blockId="12.[264,577,1188,1214]" box="[264,577,1188,1214]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[264,577,1188,1214]" fontSize="11" level="6" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="0">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,577,1188,1214]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Mayr" authorityName="Mayr" box="[351,577,1188,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,499,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Leptothorax</emphasis>
Mayr
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1323,1263,1409]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The ant genus 
<taxonomicName box="[441,584,1263,1288]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[441,584,1263,1288]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Leptothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formerly comprised a large and heterogeneous assemblage of species but 
<bibRefCitation author="Bolton" box="[405,573,1303,1329]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Bolton, B. (2003) Synopsis and classification of Formicidae. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 71, 1 - 370." type="journal article" year="2003">
Bolton (
<number box="[503,565,1303,1329]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
redefined it to include only those species closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius. Most" authorityName="Fabricius. Most" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acervorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. acervorum</emphasis>
Fabricius. Most
</taxonomicName>
California species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1075,1218,1343,1368]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1075,1218,1343,1368]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Leptothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are now assigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mayr" authorityName="Mayr" box="[403,627,1383,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[403,557,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Temnothorax</emphasis>
Mayr
</taxonomicName>
(see below), with two species remaining in 
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1286,1383,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Leptothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1286,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Leptothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
